Diagnostic and treatment principles, methods and tactics of general and abdominal surgical diseases. The course is a part of the subject "Surgery" (12 ECTS).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach the epidemiology, etiology, clinical picture, possible complications, diagnostics, treatment principles, prognosis and prophylaxis of common surgical diseases of the abdominal cavity.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student knows  1) the epidemiology, etiology,pathogenesis and prophylaxis of more frequent surgical diseases; 2) the clinical picture and possible complications of surgical diseases; 3) contemporary clinical, laboratory and instrumental methods  of patient investigation; 4) treatment methods, incl operative treatment, and indications for their usage. The student is able to 1) take the anamnesis, carry out clinical examinations of a surgical patient and to analyse the results of general clinical tests; 2) draw up a plan for laboratory and instrumental examinations and analyse their results; 3) make clinical diagnosis, explain it on the basis of differential diagnosis; 4) determine indications for conservative or surgical treatment; 5) choose a method for operative treatment according to pathological changes.
